      <hedline>
        <hl1>Lesson for the Church</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Inga Karliner letter says we are learning that, like everyone else, some priests are celibate and some are not, which means that people cannot be disconnected from biology (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Cardinal Avery Dulles (Op-Ed, June 10) says a married priesthood ''would bring in'' problems like ''adultery, divorce or contraception.'' Priests would have to live in the real world. Shouldn't that help them be more empathic and to do a better job?</p>
        <p>EDD DOERR  Silver Spring, Md., June 10, 2002</p>
      </block>
